-- Mellanox Shares Jump to Record High, Narrowing Gap With U.S.
-- B y   D a v i d   W a i n e r
-- 2012-04-22T14:04:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-22/mellanox-shares-jump-to-record-high-narrowing-gap-with-u-s-1-.html
Mellanox Technologies Ltd. (MLNX) , a
developer of technology used to transfer and store data quickly,
advanced to the highest level on record, narrowing  the gap with
its U.S.-traded shares.  The  shares  of the Yokneam Elit, Israel-based company gained
10.2 percent to 229 shekels, or the equivalent of $61.06, at the
4:30 p.m. close in Tel Aviv. Mellanoxâ€™s stock in  New York  closed
at $61.52 on April 20 after soaring a record 52 percent the
previous day.  The Israeli adapter maker forecast second-quarter sales of
between $125 million and $130 million, exceeding the $83.4
million median estimate of 10 analysts surveyed by Bloomberg.
Sales increased to a record $88.7 million in the first quarter,
while net income rose to $12.4 million after a loss of $1.6
million in the year-earlier period.  To contact the reporter on this story:
